#include <limits>

std::numberic_limits<T>::min()
std::numberic_limits<T>::max()
std::numberic_limits<T>::lowest()

<T> - is a placeholder for the type which you want to know for the min, max, lowest

Example 

Floating point
-3.40282e+38		0	1.17549e-38		3.40282e+38
lowest				min			max

Signed Integer
			0	-32768			32767
lowest				min			max

Unsigned Integer(short)
			0	0			65535
lowest				min			max


